<br>
You will need at least 1 VERY strong group (I would suggest level 60's, nice heavy tank, cleric, shaman, and some damage dealers plus yourself).  It CAN be done by one group but the mobs that drop it are not easy.<br>
<br>
Jump into the water (glee, fighting underwater =\ ).  In my experience it seems easiest to start from the West Wastes side, drop into the well overlooking the pool and start from there.  You are looking for Neriad Maidens &amp; Mistresses.  (I THINK the shawl can drop off either, but I'm pretty sure mine dropped off a Maiden.)  These range in level from 52-56ish, so I recommend using Glamour to mez, cuz a resist or an immune will mean your death.  These things hit for 290ish or better and have LOTS of hitpoints.<br>
<br>
I don't know where in SG is the best place to look cuz my experience there is kinda limited as well.  But keep to the water, cuz the mermaids cannot come out onto dry land <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
SG is not one of my favorite zones (I hate fighting in the water, it's hell on casters) so I haven't spent a lot of time there to tell you how rare it is and whatnot.  However, I've seen about 30 of the Neriads die and only 1 shawl drop, and know of several enchanters who try to hunt there all the time for this item and have had no luck.  Can't tell ya how shocked and thrilled I was to see mine drop <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
It's just not an easy to camp, which sucks cuz it really is nice - can't beat 25cha on your shoulder.  The effect is just nice for showing off and making other chanters jealous.<br>
<br>
